v>Not just any cancer, lung cancer. After claiming that lung cancer "takes 50 years to kill people, if it does", it killed him in a single year from the first 'shortness of breath' indication that led to his diagnosis. Almost as if hubris is an accelerant...</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/b7pAmGx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ButtBot9900]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Self wedging lvl100</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xI4dh8O</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pV5uyTY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xI4dh8O</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Stolenthieves]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9STVQal</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/d5BXmqQ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link : https://twitter.com/elizaorlins/status/1494128060605648897?s=20&t=0wO9AxvnDTHg9UIb4HOjLw</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rOHI24b.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9STVQal</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mech0T1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>An alternative view of the Taj Mahal and it's surroundings</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/A7Dzj8b</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/r31agxn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/A7Dzj8b</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GiftDrifter]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>So I did a thing (Day 2)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XfpfyLQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qO9lynx.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Part 1: https://imgur.com/gallery/VjFNr0y
Ignoring workers' rights opened a can of worms.

While I am waiting for the NLRB agent to get back to me about my pending filed charge, it was made sure that every coworker knows about their rights to discuss wages. Office manager was out for the day, so getting this 'policy change' officially posted (and subsiquentially recorded for recordkeeping) will take another day. Thus, I am making this post to put together my findings. 

Before the incident, I have gathered that what had happened were three different situations. The most important of them being where a patron asked an employee how much they made. They answered honestly which caused an uproar with said patron, who was a prominent VIP of our workplace (we are a semi-membership-based country club.) Details afterward were uncertain, but seemed to be the final straw tat made this policy become into place. 

The second incident was when our secondary manager has left, leaving a wide gap in responsibility and pay, which the former was dumped onto another coworker, and the latter was conveniently withheld. Tensions rose with this decision, especially with the amount of work being added with little to no increase in pay. Long arguments about this situation consequentially became commonplace with the fact that no one became fired means that the boss actually *needs* us.

The last incident is when a newly-hired coworker who went above and beyond their job description is making at least 50% more in wages than their coworkers, but that wasn't exactly troubling, just how the information got brought up and began spreading.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/D8j9ql1.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Now that I knew that the bosses didn't want us discussing our wages, I began to directly ask others. Some haven't had a raise in 13 years of being here. I am still making the minimum amount for my position after 3 and brand new hires make the same amount as I do. This discussion allows us to better gauge our worth which will better allow us to negotiate our compensation. This is a small business with barely 20 people if that many here at once. The turnover is so high that it is difficult to determine the actual number currently employed or in the system. Though it is also a multimillion dollar business which has greatly improved due to the efforts of the team who does stay.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/glDb17b.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Every accusation is an admission of guilt as they say. It turns out that our boss has been repeatedly fired or forced to quit from other smaller businesses in our industry due to moments where invoices are ran a bit too high, there is missing money in a safe, or flat out giving away supplies for free to their friends. In a personal incident, there was a patron who enjoyed the product we have provided for them and gave our boss $1000 to split amongst the team. I got $20, as did four of my other coworkers. Other incidents include a check that was given by the patron who specified that it was meant to be included into the commission pool for all fo our coworkers (all non-manager front-of-house staff get a shared 22% commission on events.) We didn't see a cent of that even a month later. 

In either case, I now wait beside my phone, hoping that the National Labor Relations Board agent would call me back soon, because there is so much going on that I am not sue if I should call them again, or the news. 

I apologize for the incomplete recollection of the events and situation. This is as much as I can remember right now and putting it into words would allow for me to better recall the details. But yeah, it seems like our boss tried to intimidate us by forgetting that we had rights, only for that to slowly blow up in his face. We will see what happens.

Edit: I heard back from my board agent! The charges have been docketed and I have a case number and everything! On top of that, I have another agent talking to me about how to join the Service Employees International Union and have just sent my paperwork! Things are moving fast!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XfpfyLQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[1garret322]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Is this true?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ug2GxZD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9dgrLaJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Did Limbaugh really mock the dead?

(originally posted by @CassySpencer on 2021-02-18 10:12:30)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ug2GxZD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThisTimeLastYear]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>They are! Just ask Dain Ironfoot</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mXvK2Tt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tvfiHKA.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He's bacon for trouble.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/mXvK2Tt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Herebychoice]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Wearing the fur of my enemies</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Qbfpxln</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2DNSsas.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Qbfpxln</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[anlyin]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>There was some type of logic.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/am3bRD9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/T7b1q7E.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8SMY0Sk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/am3bRD9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeirdAlisMySpiritUserName]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>We need to do better as a society.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ATGgDeL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jPwiMqa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ATGgDeL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[neoswhiterabbitt]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>